GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 1066
Short Title: Child Care Stabilization & Affordability Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Helfrich, Lofton, Prather, and von Haefen (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 29, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PERMIT OPPORTUNITY SCHOLARSHIP FUNDS TO BE AWARDED FOR
3 PREKINDERGARTEN; TO MAKE PERMANENT THE TRI-SHARE CHILD CARE
4 PILOT PROGRAM; TO REENACT THE CHILD CARE TAX CREDIT; TO EXPAND
5 THE EARLY CHILDHOOD EDUCATION WORKFORCE; TO STREAMLINE
6 ADMINISTRATIVE REQUIREMENTS FOR CHILD CARE PROVIDERS; TO UTILIZE
7 PUBLIC FACILITIES FOR CHILD CARE; TO CLARIFY REGULATORY GUIDANCE
8 FOR RELIGIOUS CHILD CARE PROGRAMS; TO STABILIZE CHILD CARE
9 FUNDING AND BENEFITS IN NORTH CAROLINA; AND TO ENHANCE CHILD
10 CARE WORKFORCE COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS.
11 Whereas, affordable and accessible child care is essential to workforce participation,
12 small business stability, and economic growth across the State; and
13 Whereas, North Carolina faces significant shortages in licensed child care capacity
14 due to workforce constraints, regulatory bottlenecks, and rising operating costs; and
15 Whereas, early childhood educators are often paid wages insufficient to sustain the
16 workforce needed to meet statewide demand; and
17 Whereas, expanding training pathways, including apprenticeships and community
18 college programs, can strengthen the child care workforce pipeline; and
19 Whereas, the lack of coordinated administrative systems requires child care providers
20 to interact with multiple agencies and funding streams; and
21 Whereas, the General Assembly has a compelling interest in expanding safe,
22 high-quality child care while ensuring regulatory clarity, workforce development, and economic
23 participation; Now, therefore,
24 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
25
